codes_lines_covered: let b: u8 = 32;
assert_eq!(is_valid(b), true);
let b: u8 = 126; // Less than 127, valid
assert_eq!(is_valid(b), true);
let b: u8 = 127; // Equals 127, not valid
assert_eq!(is_valid(b), false);
let b: u8 = b'\t'; // Tab character, valid
assert_eq!(is_valid(b), true);
let b: u8 = 128; // Greater than 127, valid
assert_eq!(is_valid(b), true);
let input: u8 = 32; // satisfying the constraint: b >= 32
assert!(is_valid(input)); // expect true because 32 is valid
let input: u8 = 127; // satisfying the constraint: b != 127 is false
assert!(!is_valid(input)); // expect false because 127 is not valid
let input: u8 = b'\t'; // satisfying the condition: b == b'\t'
assert!(is_valid(input)); // expect true because tab character is valid
let input: u8 = b'\t'; // corresponds to the ASCII value of tab
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), true);
let input: u8 = 31; // below the minimum valid range (32)
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), false);
let input: u8 = 127; // equals the value that should return false
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), false);
let input: u8 = 32; // minimum valid character (space)
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), true);
let input: u8 = 33; // above tab and valid
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), true);
let input: u8 = 128; // above normal valid range
assert_eq!(is_valid(input), true);
